<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-686] GroovyServlet will crash if parameters are passed in HTTP Request</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-686</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If parameters are being passed to a groovy servlet the servlet crashes with MissingPropertyException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This behaviour has been introduced with version 1.4 ( most current ) of groovy.lang.Binding. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is, that GroovyServlet tries to determine the state of a variable by executing getVairable() method, which throws the exception if the variable can not be found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll send the patch to the developer mailing list.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
